- .github/workflows/deploy-docs-preview.yml (new file)

Context:
The existing `deploy-docs.yml` deploys to production on push to main. This adds preview deploys for PRs.

Cloudflare Pages supports branch deploys natively. The Wrangler action's `pages deploy` command returns a deployment URL. We can extract it and post as a PR comment.

```yaml
name: Docs Preview

on:
  pull_request:
    paths: ['docs/**']

permissions:
  contents: read
  pull-requests: write

jobs:
  preview:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v5

      - uses: actions/setup-node@v5
        with:
          node-version: 22

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm install
        working-directory: docs

      - name: Build docs
        run: npm run build
        working-directory: docs

      - name: Deploy preview
        id: deploy
        uses: cloudflare/wrangler-action@v3
        with:
          apiToken: ${{ secrets.CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN }}
          accountId: ${{ secrets.CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID }}
          command: pages deploy docs/out --project-name=opentabs-docs --branch=${{ github.head_ref }}

      - name: Comment preview URL
        uses: actions/github-script@v7
        with:
          script: |
            const body = `## Docs Preview\n\nPreview deployed: ${process.env.DEPLOYMENT_URL}\n\n_This preview was generated from the latest commit on this PR._`;
            // Find existing comment to update
            const { data: comments } = await github.rest.issues.listComments({
              owner: context.repo.owner, repo: context.repo.repo, issue_number: context.issue.number
            });
            const existing = comments.find(c => c.body?.includes('## Docs Preview'));
            if (existing) {
              await github.rest.issues.updateComment({
                owner: context.repo.owner, repo: context.repo.repo, comment_id: existing.id, body
              });
            } else {
              await github.rest.issues.createComment({
                owner: context.repo.owner, repo: context.repo.repo, issue_number: context.issue.number, body
              });
            }
        env:
          DEPLOYMENT_URL: ${{ steps.deploy.outputs.deployment-url }}
```

The `--branch` flag tells Cloudflare Pages to create a branch deploy (preview) instead of updating production. Each branch gets a unique URL like `<branch>.opentabs-docs.pages.dev`.

The comment step updates an existing comment if found (avoids comment spam on force-pushes).

Note: Check the exact output variable name from `cloudflare/wrangler-action@v3` — it might be `deployment-url` or `url`. Read the action's docs or outputs.

Constraints:
- Requires CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN and CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID secrets (already configured for deploy-docs.yml)
- The preview project name must match the production project name (opentabs-docs)
- Do NOT modify the existing deploy-docs.yml
